m of politics; and about many other issues. By demonstrating the deep relevance of Veblen’s writings to today's political troubles, The Political Ideas of Thorstein Veblen offers an important reconsideration of a major American thinker.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Classes & Economic Disparity.2bisacsh1 aTilman, Rick, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030015999840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030016338440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300163384423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300163384/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY